1:7.answer:
This verse from Chapter 1 carries a profound spiritual message. . "Know also, O best among the twice-born! the names of those
who are the most distinguished amongst ourselves, the leaders of my army;
these I name to thee for thy information. The deeper meaning points to the soul's journey through material existence. In the Vedantic tradition, every verse of the Gita operates on multiple levels — the literal (describing the battlefield), the ethical (guiding right action), and the metaphysical (revealing the nature of reality). This particular teaching invites the seeker to look beyond surface appearances and perceive the eternal truth that underlies all transient phenomena.
